place_description: Summit Coffee's flagship store in downtown Davidson, North Carolina, this cafe serves coffee roasted locally by Summit, plus in-house baked goods, beer and wine and more.

reviews_data.review_text: Terrible coffee, fun place.
Very cool I witnessed a music open mic tons if guitars in the crowd. The dirty Chai I got wasn't great but the musical talent was impressive
Been a fan for a long time . Great coffee, pretty solid pastries. Loved the granola don't sleep on the tomato / cheese pastry
One of the places I miss most from living in Davidson. The baristas are so friendly and the vibes are wonderful.

Great spot with a nice quiet patio and concerts at the back on the weekends.
2 heads-up:
- for some reasons, this location never has any snacks...either they don't stock enough or it goes away very fast...but we went there MANY times...and always faced the same situation.
- something you will find at most of their locations...the staff changes all the time, and isn't always trained properly...
Result: your coffee goes from good to ok...
Employee retention doesn't seem to be a focus...that will have some long-term impacts when competitors have stable and pleasant staff.
Quick and tasty coffee in a campy, rustic atmosphere including outdoor area that lives up to its name "Basecamp."
Good coffee, nice amount of space upstairs to work, play a board game or chill. Cookie was yummy.
Best chocolate croissants
good latte

The atmosphere is cozy but the seats aren't very comfortable. The waiters are nice and it my 2 of my drinks came out fast. My coffee came out very slow and the workers pretty much forgot about it. My hot cocoa was very watered down. It was ok.

I absolutely love stopping here before or after work!!! Try the birthday cookie!! Absolutely yummy!!! We ate them too fast to show!!
Also I am not a coffee drinker, but I love the hot Chai tea with oatmilk! Absolutely delicious!!!

I visited for the first time today to pick up a bag of coffee, and I must say, the experience exceeded my expectations. The warm and genuine smiles from the staff were a refreshing contrast to the often-disconnected interactions we encounter in a world filled with discontent. It's amazing how such a simple gesture can leave such a lasting impression. The shop itself has a welcoming ambiance, with a cozy vibe that makes you want to linger a little longer. The staff was knowledgeable and eager to help me choose the perfect blend, making the experience not just a transaction but a genuine interaction. The quality of the separate cup of coffee I purchased speaks for itself, rich and aromatic, and I'm already looking forward to brewing my first cup at home. Overall, I couldn't be happier with my visit and will definitely be back. This is the kind of place that turns a simple errand into an experience you'll look forward to repeating. Highly recommended!
We come here for coffee every Sunday before church. Our favorites are the Tomato Feta Croissant and their scones.

Hugely over rated.  Twice, the coffee was appalling, the pastries under baked, and very surprisingly, the  service unpleasant.
There will not be a third time.

Favorite coffee shop.  I go to either Mooresville or Davidson Summit. Davidson more even though I live in Mooresville extremely close to the summit.

I am impressed with how smoothly everything runs.
Live music and performance on Thursday 7:00 PM

Plateau-tier coffee, or should I say.. peak.. or summit... I've been to nearly every coffee shop in Manhattan/New York City, and this one could trade punches with the best of them. Atmosphere/decor has improved significantly since the last time I visited -- they took constructive criticism positively and elevated their game to A-Tier. Live music has been added, upstairs is cozy, air conditioning and heating works fantastic. Highly recommended.
I love Summit coffee but the visit was not a great experience. Bad smell, poor communication, and croissant was doughy and greasey. Sad.
Great music, great coffee, great playground for kids. Central part of the community.

Summit not only has amazing coffee and delicious feta and herb scones, but they've also created a true sense of community. I love attending my run club on Wednesday and Sunday mornings and meeting up for coffee at Summit afterward. It's the perfect spot to unwind and connect with others after a good run. The welcoming atmosphere makes it so much more than just a coffee shop--it's a community hub.

What a special community gathering place this is. The staff is lovely. The atmosphere in and outside is easy-going and welcoming. I am a graduate student and I often study at Summit . I love seeing all of the staff as they are very friendly and helpful.

Love love love Summit Coffee.

Parking can be hit or miss especially on the weekends. It is street parking 2 hour max. On Saturdays there is a flourishing farmers market full of fresh veggies, food, honey, and local meats. Come early because it gets busy!

They're one of the few shops who make their own pastry. It is amazing. Fresh, delicate, buttery, incredible flavor. I highly recommend the tomato feta Danish and the blueberry scone. Try dipping bits of your scone in their rotating drip coffee. I tried sweater weather today based on Gabes recommendation.

Their lattes are awesome as well! Each cup is perfectly crafted with micro foam and a beautiful design. A++

The shop gives off chill vibes and is full of plants, an upstairs with board games, and plenty of places to sit outside.
Staff were super friendly, and the atmosphere is perfect to sit back and relax with a drink. Their tea is really yummy!
Staff were super friendly, and the atmosphere is perfect to sit back and relax with a drink. Their tea is really yummy!
My favorite place to get coffee in davidson. Awesome place to study, especially upstairs. Bring a jacket because the AC is strong but the staff is lovely and scones are delicious
Mobile order was speedy fast!!! Tried the iced pumpkin cheesecake latte and walked the Davidson farmers market on cloud 9 while sipping my yummy beverage.

I've been going to Summit Coffee to work on my research almost every other workday and every weekend, the staff is always kind and nice, great coffee (the best Mocha you'll ever have!), and upstairs has AC now!!!
The pastries are lovely, however, sometimes they're not properly covered, and you can see flies around them.  Bathrooms can definitely be cleaner. Other than that, I love this coffee shop!
The coffee was ok, their blueberry muffin was very dry. The cafe itself is adorable, bathrooms were clean, plenty of spots to sit, and the AC works VERY well!!! I'd give em a second chance

Very cute. It's in an older part of town so you get  a more rustic shop. It can get very busy on weekends due to college kids and it just being a popular place. Same with the mornings. It's a fun and very aesthetic place to be to hang out with people or get work done. The lack of booths and comfy chairs do make it hard to sit there for longer than an hour or two though if you're trying to spend a good amount of time on some work. It can also get very loud downstairs and upstairs (usually because of college kids). I recommend it more for socializing :)

The food and drinks are great. It's a little more on the pricey side (close to Starbucks in price). I like their blends of coffee much better than Dunkin donuts so if you're a coffee snob like me, I think they've got pretty good coffee. They have a couple herbal slushies and/or drinks but minimal food. The food will vary, it's always got different foods there. Sadly their avocado toast is gone from their menu.

This location was adorable and perfectly placed downtown next to a book store. Super kid friendly with coloring page menus and a small play area out back. Additional study space on the second floor. I had a cookie and one of their lavender oatmilk latte, both were delicious!

Horrible service, there was a line and the attendant was rushing customers, she didn't answer what was asked in a bad way. I ordered a hot chocolate and it was watery, with very poor quality chocolate.

I base reviews of coffee shops/cafes on two things - quality of their drip coffee and bonus points if they roast their own and offer a fresh pour over. This coffee shop has been around for over 20 years and I can see why the community loves it. Happy we got to try it while in town!
Really cute spot. It was my 1st time here. I had dark roast coffee w/Carmel and oatmilk. The coffee wasn't hot not was it strong. I'll try something different next time.
Fun quant coffee shop with a great personality. We really enjoyed the town too.

One of the worst cafes of my life, if you like being mistreated by the attendant, having horrible coffee and watery chocolate, yes this is your place, otherwise get out. Detail the AC dont work upstairs, very very hot place.
Excellent coffee and staff. I went back the next day for the same and she remembered my order!
Wonderful cappuccino!
Absolutely love this place. Such a welcoming staff and environment. Hands down the best iced vanilla latte.
Good little spot in downtown Davidson. I am not a coffee person, I usually get a London Fog.

If you LOVE cute n cozy coffee shops, this is the place to go in the area! Not only is the staff great, but so is the atmosphere. After living in nyc for a while and experiencing cute n cozy coffee shops galore, I moved to cornelius area and didnt find a cute spot for months. THEN I FOUND SUMMIT! There is also a back yard area for people to go outside.
Great coffeehouse in downtown Davidson. Fast and friendly.
Cozy atmosphere. Nice brews!
Great coffee and an even better patio! I highly recommend Summit Coffee.
Nice atmosphere in Davidson downtown. Especially the backyard is great. Not much food options. Coffee is good.
It was my first time in the shop and I enjoyed my time there today! Such a chill vibe and my mocha was refreshing! I'll be coming back!

A great place to sit down and enjoy your coffee and chit chat whole day long!
It is one of the best place in the center of Davidson Downtown.

The best chai tea around.
Friendly staff
Great coffee in a relaxed environment
Great atmosphere, but the iced latte is ~90% milk and maybe one shot of espresso. Not the kick I was expecting from a cute cafe.

I had a really good iced latte here and they were willing to make a decaf version for my daughter which isn't always the case at coffee shops.  They also offer canned and bottled drinks and some cookies/pastries.
A great family experience with a drink for kids as well! We loved it!
Recomiendo el chocolate y los postres
Summit Coffee Baristas ALWAYS find a way to show their Christmas Spirit this season!  Try the Tiramisu Latta - YUMMY!
The coffee was good! I got cappuccino in half and half. They also offer matcha which I should have next time I'm around.
Great little coffee shop with fresh roasted and specially sourced beans. Perfect shop for a small college town.
One of my favorite coffee shops. Love the style and location.
Great coffee, quite place, good to catch up with work
Super cute shop and great coffee. Scone was great too. Must come if you're in town.  Lots of seating inside and out. Walking distance to the college.
I love the atmosphere and service. Always great. I have not eaten any food, but it was a great place to get some work done.

Always love coming here for some chai or coffee, haven't had much else. But I absolutely adore the environment and the service, it's always phenomenal. I forgot to ask for oatmilk and they asked me what kind of milk i wanted, saved me an unwanted lactose intolerant mode haha!

WE HAD THE CUTEST DAY HERE!!!

Me & a friend of mine took the kiddos for a walk right down the street to grab them both a pumpkin. Then we set up a blanket behind Summit with some paints. Enjoyed some delicious coffee while the kids painted their pumpkins. They had a blast, and we got to relax a bit. There is even a little area for a slide, and they provide sidewalk chalk for the kids.  Perfect mom date idea for sure!!
They have good coffee but literally 50% of the time we go their espresso machine is either not working or being cleaned.
Very friendly and cozy atmosphere. Great, quick service. Plenty of seating and good mochas!

Came in on Labor Day weekend with a line that was out the door. The staff was super friendly and efficient, and the coffee very good. Not only that but they are also measuring their greenhouse gas emissions and disclosing them publicly, so they are serious about sustainability. They even have several initiatives for reducing their emissions over time!
Drinks weak and barista not friendly. Iced latte wasn't even full to the top. Barista slung my husband's nitro and spilt some of it. Far too expensive for a mediocre experience. Will not return.
Coffee is nothing special, but the atmosphere is great.
Ordered Americano..espresso isn't made to order. Was poured out of a glass jar.... It was done being made in less than 20 seconds.
The coffee is so so good!
Kilimanjaro espresso bean is the best!
Great coffee, appealing atmosphere, overall a great coffee shop.

Very cute little coffee shop. I was in the area and needed a snack for my 2 year old. The coffee was delicious and the breakfast muffin was huge! There's great outdoor seating and a toddler size playground behind the shop.
Tried an espresso soda for the first time, top notch!

I'm a PhD student at Clemson and live in Davidson:). I am in the middle of a really intense research project and Energy United cut our power today.  I needed a quiet place with strong WiFi today more urgently than ever before.  I was a ball of stress and the staff was so patient and helpful with me.  Right now this is the only way I have to show how grateful I am and how much I appreciated their help today.  I will find a couple of other ways later, LoL:)
Always great coffee.  Sometimes a bit of a line.
Iced coffee was perfect
Love the chill atmosphere and just tried the "summer camp" coffee
Awesome atmosphere, great latte!
Great hometown coffee shop. Loved the singer songwriter showcase!

I have gone here three times and the staff has never been friendly. I figured it was maybe an off day but that's not the case. They appear to be young college kids who don't understand customer service. The coffee is also some of the worst I have ever had. I typically drink iced coffee and the sugar tastes very odd in their drinks. Last but not least, the place is woke and has a BLM sign still on the front window.

There are many better spots close by.

The staff here were very kind and knowledgeable. The coffee beans I bought were roasted only 3 days prior - they were very tasty and fresh! When purchasing, they offer to grind the beans for you, with your choice of fine , coarse, or somewhere between. The grind I received was extremely consistent, fresh, and tasted amazing. I bought the "Basecamp" roast and was additionally given a free drip coffee with my purchase. A very pleasant experience, I will be returning.
Great fresh drip coffee. In Historic Davidson.
What a cool little place Beverages were great. They had a guy out back singing really relaxing evening down south

Yo! These baristas were so nice and accommodating. They're all trained up to make stellar drinks. The vegan pumpkin chocolate e muffin-top was one of my favorite things and I had 5 or 6 while we were visiting over the weekend.
The croissant had great flavor but very dense.
Fun coffee place that serves beer on tap and wine and bakery items. Eclectic and very friendly!

Amazing place! I recommend the Strawberry Creme Foam Coffee! Well decorated with a modern feel. It has an upstairs which is a great place to study! If you're in the mood for a little sun and don't mind a little bit of chatter in the background, they also have a spacious space in the back!
Drinks came out quick and tasted good Chai Latte was amazing. The cookie is a can't miss. The atmosphere was great!
We had the fruit loop latte and the unicorn soda! They also have a great playground for kids on property. They regularly have live music on the patio as well!
Cappuccino was good but chai latte was terrible.
They have some good coffee but these guys don't know how to run a business. Ran into bunch of subscription issues. Their stores usually out of of stock on most coffee. It is a total mess

The much-needed renovations are outstanding. There is so much more light here, seating is better and the vibes are more cheerful and less rustic, which had been a little tooo old timey/Cracker Barrel vibes. Everyone raves about the coffee, but I love the chai and scones (especially the savory ones).
Favorite coffee shop in the Davidson area. Slightly higher than normal prices but great drinks.
Went for open mic night. My daughter's first public performance! Chai latte was very tasty. Especially if you like spices.
Amazing coffee! High quality coffee with a nice atmosphere.
Great local coffee place in the area. Definitely have to try the birthday cake cookies, they are amazing. We especially love coming to trivia nights upstairs on Thursdays.
Coffee is delicious and staff is really friendly!
Such a cozy spot, fantastic service and of course great coffee. Love it here!
Local interessante para apreciadores de cafe . Ideal para abrir um laptop e ler alguma coisa.

Find your summit! This quiet cafe has excellent service, patient staff and wonderful  decor.  Backs up to the farmers market on Saturday and has a tasteful vanilla oat milk latte.  Their vegan pumpkin bar is delicious!
Great little coffee shop. Had a cider beer on the patio.  Would go back
Great place to visit and relax
I love the coffee here! Should have more desserts. More Music ! Cmon, this space deserves a good environment and good music can do it. Here is my recommendations.  Just missing it!
Nice place, but the espresso was so horrible!
The best latte in North America to say the least. Most European place in NC!
Nicely decorated place which doesn't get cleaned. Vents are full of cobwebs and dust. Bathrooms are unkempt. Light fixtures are dusty. Sanitation is in question.

Coffee is good and they have a few other options if needed. Space is small but quaint. Only complaint is the drinks are priced very high. Summit beans are good but they are relatively expensive for the flavor.
My friend took me here while I was in town and it was pretty good coffee. The staff weren't very friendly. Cozy location, but small, so with our stroller we felt rushed.
Cute hidding place.
Went there for open mic night. Not only was the atmosphere wonderful, but the drinks were good too. Definitely coming back next week
Holy cows!  Strong coffee and not bitter at all!  Davidson, NC!  University town!  Live performance, too!
Friendly.
We went for family fun day. Great and friendly staff and good exhibits.
Great place to relax with a friend.
It's an eclectic coffee shop that has developed some very... interesting flavors! I got a H&H London Fog. It was pretty good.
Great coffee
Great Coffee
Nice spot. But music is loud AF. I couldn't even do my work it was so loud.

Even though it was a Saturday Farmers Market day and the line was wrapped around the building. The staff was kind, friendly, and and worked as fast as they could. The coffee, hot or cold, is worth the wait.
very friendly!!!

beautiful cafe in the heart of downtown davidson. the baristas were friendly and skilled, the shop has a great atmosphere with lots of natural light, and plenty of indoor and outdoor seating. the espresso is delicious, and i love the pared down, sophisticated menu! will definitely be back.
Great local coffee. Oat and almond milks available. You can also grab a drink and pastry!
Great little shop off Main Street to get some coffee and work or read. Immaculate vibes.
Friendly atmosphere and a variety of options. Espresso was more bitter than I prefer, but latte was great. Dog friendly out back.
Great outdoor space with live music.
Best coffee in Davidson
Everything tastes good. A Davidson staple!
We love stopping in to Summit when we're in Davidson! Love their coffee and the patio out back. Great draft beer options too once 4pm (or 3?) rolls around.
I hadn't been to Summit Coffee in many years. It was nice to see the light and airy updated interior design.

Coffee menu is very limited. I was in the store for literally 2 seconds before the unfriendly cashier with the bad hair told she/he could take my order outside because dogs were not allowed. My dog wasn't walking on the floor he was in carrier not bothering anyone. This place is not dog friendly. Every other store on the block was dog welcoming they even have water available for the dogs.. It's ashamed such a nice place but rude workers and no customer service.
Great outdoor space to grab a few beers or have a coffee.
Great service, nice atmosphere! My drink was made well, too!

Coffee tastes great, service is ok. Small details which makes one choose Summit next time over other places on Main Street however were not there:
I visited on Wednesday at about 1.30
I wanted to grab a coffee and quick snack. The baked goods cabinet was pretty empty, no savory to choose from. I was told they had bagels. Then she checked and they were out of bagels. Which is okay if Summit offers bagels in the morning only but that was not was I was told.
Last thing: The entrance is a beautiful old door, but it doesn't work! I had three or four attempts to enter before a guest finally let me in after seeing me struggle to get in. There were three people behind the counter not busy at the time who did not see me trying to missing t all.
Note: old doors a beautiful and I understand they might be hard to fix. This one has no handle on it and it wouldn't open when you push it hard. So maybe a note on the door telling me how to enter would be useful. I started to think Summit was closed and almost walked away when the guest helped me.
As far as snacks: it would be nice if there were more bagels, croissants or a pack of almonds or something Summit offered for those who wanted savory and to fill up the baked cabinet instead of having nothing to offer. If there are no choices early afternoon people will go elsewhere next time even if they want to support local coffee shops.
I hope this review is helpful.
Have a great day.
Great little coffee joint with cool drinks and an even cooler aesthetic! Absolutely killer drinks, and a must have for anyone, from coffee aficionados to just getting a cup of joe.
Cute coffee shop! Loved the light roast!
a wonderful coffee shop that i love to stop by when i have the time!
Such friendly people and a fun, eclectic vibe. Home baked goodies looked amazing.
Chai latte was really good. I like the vibe of this place. Very old cool building.
Great vibe! Coffee isn't award winning but they have all the usuals and even sell adult beverages which is a big plus.

I like coming here to drink a coffee every time I come, but this time I came and I ordered a cappuccino, it was horrible, it felt like the coffee was old and they heated it up. It tasted horrible and plus the size of it was very little!
They have decaf iced coffee and like nobody else offers that!! It was also good :)
Just grabbed a latte and some hot chocolate for my kids. Great service and ambiance here. Always enjoy hanging out on the back patio.
One of my local favs.  This time I switched it up and got a mint today. 10 out of 10!
Excellent coffee, pastries, and service. Totally recommended!
We love the environment of Summit. The outdoor seating out back offers a great place to congregate with friends and enjoy a drink.
Supporting Small Business Saturday with cold and hot drinks. Service was pleasant and swift.
Didn't like the coffee, weak and burnt. Also it was $5.00 for a small. I'll stick with Duncan doughnuts. I'm a cheap date.
Very cute Cafe, was crowded but the wait wasn't too long. The vegan pumpkin muffin and lattes were great!
Great customer service, excellent experience, cozy local coffee place
Delicious coffee, super friendly people, great refill price!
What a fun old building which adds to the charm of this coffee house.. good light breakfast items and atmosphere
The espresso is legit
Consistently good with coffee and tea
Love that place!!
Great drinks
Love this place!! Download their app for some great deals & you don't have to wait in line if you order ahead

8 years ago this place served counter culture coffee. It was the best coffee I have ever tasted. Then they started roasting their own coffee and it is now the worst coffee I have ever tasted. I  Did not think it was possible to make a cup of coffee that tastes worse than Starbucks but they have succeeded.. Summit coffee used to be full of life and soul. Now. Now it's the one place in Davidson I avoid  Out of respect for what it once was.

I have a very dear friend who can not wear a mask because of doctor's orders. She is Medically exempt. HOWEVER last Friday she was harassed and treated rudely by employees . You need to teach your employees  that not everything is black or white but in shades of gray and for God's Sake be kind!
Pleasant staff, nice outdoor seating, popular downtown Davidson location, parking is a little tricky, drip coffee was good but a little pricey.
My husband absolutely loves this place for the live entertainment. The coffee is good. Selection of beers: IPA & wine are nice. Great place to unwind after a long day!

Really nice people Ina froo-froo atmosphere. The couple in front of me spent five minutes talking to the employee about sugar content of all the different milk substitutes that were possible for their coffees as though it made any difference at all. Silly. It was way cooler when the theme was climber-cool ... No one uses the project board anymore but the coffee is good. Just get a cup of black coffee and move on!

Service was great. Staff was friendly. Prices are typical. Got a latte and it tasted good.

Location is small, but it's a nice spot for some coffee to go, or to sit and hang if you're lucky to snag a seat. I gave it four stars because I found the syrups/flavors to be a little lacking. They had the typical flavors and two seasonal flavors which were a bit off (exotic?)of a pairing in my opinion.

Overall I was happy with my experience.
Love their renovation and the outside offers a place to drink wine or coffee and let your kids run freely.
Soul of Davidson
Great coffee shop.
I like the ice coffee. I prefer mine black and this one stands by itself.
Great coffee , and delicious scones (tried lemon lavender and chocolate chips).
Coffee is great! Friday Nights there is live music and great drink selection.
Very cozy, quaint, and chill place to work and catch up on calls, and sip a macchiato.
Love this quaint little cafe.  Very casual and friendly and has the BEST chocolate chip cookies ever!
Great service and a wonderful assortment of well-crafted coffee beverages.
Excellent coffee and friendly service. I do wish that they still offered Hazelnut flavoring, but it doesn't change my rating!
The new patio area and relocated play area are completed. Great place to sip a beverage and listen to live music outdoors.

Very awesome place, good people and patrons as I could see and tell by the lil time I was in there on a few occasions, great location, parking is hit and miss, but if you're patient you'll get a spot close and it's worth it, outdoor seating and entertainment on certain days and evenings, I wouldn't go there if the coffee wasn't good and they have some alcohol choices if you are in that kinda mood
Summit is great. Just visited today for the first time since I was a student at Davidson years ago. Still great coffee and I love the upstairs area. Keep up and keep expanding, Summit!
After experiences with masks and being accosted by the employees over such,  no amount of, or quality taste of coffee would ever garner my support for this establishment again.
Always great to visit!
Low energy this day. Not normal. Forgot cream and sugar.

The band was great! Some of the best bluegrass I've heard lately!
One of the bathroom doors seemed to be locked all night.
Always try to stop by for a coffee. Good coffee and great service. Great location.
Delicious coffee, cozy environment.
Love this place. Super nice people, great coffee, and an app that makes on the go pickup a breeze.
Nice cozy spot, good coffee.  Good for a sit down n chat!
The coffee isn't the best but the hot coco is good.

Excellent coffee in a very relaxing and cozy atmosphere! I had a mocha latte and my boyfriend had a cappuccino and an espresso shot. Everything was made to perfection! My boyfriend has managed coffee shops and he said this was one of the best espresso pulls he's had. On top of that, they also have beer and wine! Definitely worth a trip (and many more)

Best vanilla raspberry latte I've ever had!

...and I've had a lot of them!
Really cozy place and lattes there are really good. Upstairs are pretty quite to study/work. Definitely a go to place in Davidson!

They got me hooked on the srongest cup of coffee I've had in a long time.

9/10 quick service, tasty & strong coffee, and good early morning hours.

Love the atmosphere, the delicious coffee and treats. We bought my mother in law a bag of decaf coffee for Christmas as its her favorite coffee around this area and the order came with a free cup of coffee. Definitely a little more on the expensive side, but it is always quality ingredients and the staff know their stuff!

After this being the 3rd visit and the 3rd horrible experience I had to write a review. The staff really takes their time and seem to be lazy, I have been told they didn't have a drink just cause they didn't want to make it. Today I went in for the first time in a year thinking I would give it a try, I was the first person in line and no one in the coffee shop as I'm waiting for coffee it starts to get busy they served 6 different costumers before I finally had enough and asked for a refund, the girl said she didn't know how. Left me sitting there for another ten to figure it out and was still unsuccessful. I had to call the bank to get a refund. If you want a beer and a nice patio to chill on maybe this place could work for you.  But don't bother coming here if your a coffee enthusiast  or have other plans that day.

Summit Coffee is always a great place to enjoy a good cup of coffee and some time with friends. While the first floor doesn't have a lot of room, between the upstairs and the area outside, it makes for a great place to hangout.
Great hot chocolate!

The coffee was excellent as well as the service. Even more impressive was the chocolate chip scone. I was expecting a typical scone, drab with some chocolate chips, only to find the most delicious, buttery pastry in my mouth. The taste resembled that of a shortbread cookie and was fabulous! I wish I had the recipe.
Yummy
Cozy little coffee shop that also has wine and beer.  Fantastic outdoor area for live music with lights at night for a warm environment with friends and loved ones.
The management generously satisfied my request to introduce me to the  variety of flavored syrups which provided an exotic customized tea experience
Great coffee and nice sitting area outback!
Nice, small town vibe and friendly customer service. Coffee is delicious, too.
Best grilled cheese I have ever had.

I came here yesterday and tried a new tea flavor and when I tasted it and didn't love it, the barista didn't hesitate to offer a replacement! I fully expected to have to pay for a new drink. I will continue to drive half an hour to come here whenever I want a great sit down coffee experience. 5 stars every time.
Terrific iced skim latte.  Not burned flavor like DD ..got some roasted beans.
I Love the Chai Tea. It has an awesome outdoor space with plenty of seating.
Go for the coffee, the tea, and the ambiance!
Some of the best coffee I've had in a very long time!  I will be going back.
Well equiped staff.  High quality coffee.  Great location.
The shop itself is great and rustic.  Coffee is great.  Staff is friendly.  Bought a bag of their light roast beans and is awesome!
Amazing coffee! Stopped here during my road trip and everything was amazing. Great customer service, great coffee and pastries.
Awesoooome! Thx Summit Coffee for the great cup of Cortado!
Every town in America should have a place like this.
Nice restaurant,good food and friendly staff

Great coffee awesome blueberry muffins everyone there is so friendly and so helpful and every Friday and Saturday night they have incredible music out on the stage this is a red gem in the middle of Davidson I highly recommend going there
Fantastic coffee excellent service. Plenty of parking and outdoor seating. Friendly neighborhood and good place to hang out and work.
Best coffee spot in downtown. Good drinks and the best study spot, always lots of high school and college students around during the school year.
Great little coffee house in downtown Davidson. They also have an outdoor patio and serve beer...I guess for when you need to take the edge off drining too much coffee
Great staff.
Great coffee, friendly staff, great atmosphere
Great coffee and equally great atmosphere. Take your drink out back on Saturday mornings. The kids can enjoy the playground while you enjoy your coffee and the farmers market!
Good service and great coffee
always good.

As a total coffee lover and addict, Summit is one of the best coffee shops in town. The beans are fresh because you can taste it and the baristas know how to make great coffee drinks.

Hip, cozy place but may be hard to find seatings on the weekend.
Slowest service possible. The barista was more worried about gossiping with her coworkers than making a simple drink.
